item.value: A map entry (key-value pair). The <tt>Map.entrySet<tt> method returns a collection-view of the map, whose elements are of this class. The <i>only<i> way to obtain a reference to a map entry is from the iterator of this collection-view. These <tt>Map.Entry<tt> objects are valid <i>only<i> for the duration of the iteration; more formally, the behavior of a map entry is undefined if the backing map has been modified after the entry was returned by the iterator, except through the <tt>setValue<tt> operation on the map entry. @see MapentrySet() @since 1.2
